# User Experience Rules

## Response Requirements
- **Concise answers**: Step-by-step instructions for procedural queries
- **Clickable citations**: Direct links to source files and line ranges
- **Copy-ready commands**: Commands that can be executed directly
- **Context preservation**: Maintain source context in responses

## User Interface Elements
- **Feedback prompt**: "Was this helpful?" with rating system
- **Fallback suggestions**: Alternative queries when no results found
- **Progress indicators**: Show processing status for long operations
- **Error handling**: Clear, actionable error messages

## Navigation & Actions
- **File opening**: Direct links to open files in editor
- **Explorer integration**: Reveal files in file system
- **Search history**: Track and suggest previous queries
- **Bookmarking**: Save useful responses for later reference

## Implementation Guidelines
- Use consistent design patterns across all UI components
- Implement responsive design for various screen sizes
- Provide keyboard shortcuts for power users
- Include accessibility features (ARIA labels, screen reader support)
- Test user flows with real team members
